g.text: “The patients expect too much from doctors, their think doctors should care about them and always stand on their points, but we should concen-trate on treatment”
“Things related to treatment are hard to understand for many patients, so we have to use very simple language to explain it and keep repeating to ensure that they understand”
“It’s hard to remember details of every patient, we need to refer to the medical history repeatedly, and to check their schedule to remind them”

PatientQ1: Can you simply talk about your daily lives in hospital?Q2: Please introduce daily treatment? What do you do beside treatment?Q3: Is there anywhere that you are not satisfied and not convenient? (on the hospital condition and medical workers)Q4: Who take care of the patients and what should they do?

Medical workerQ1: What are your daily works, and when do you talk to patients directly?Q2: How patients think of you, are there any conflicts?Q3: What kind of medical workers can get well along with patients?
“Illness and boring routine in hospital made me in bad mood. Sometimes doctors with bad attitude made my negative mood worse”
“I want to know my state of illness and my schedule for treatment, so I want to talk with doctor frequently”
“It’s very hard to take care of myself without others’ help, I cannot move freely, and the nurses are very busy”
